How to get certified

Your work—our recognition.
It's that simple

The Wix Studio Certification program recognizes web creators who demonstrate deep knowledge and create high-quality websites. There are no tests, no applications and no extra steps—just your work speaking for itself.

What we do:

Every month, we scout Wix Studio creators who meet our standards of excellence and welcome them to the Studio League, our community of certified experts.

Then what?

Once certified, you’ll get an email, fill in a quick form, and you’re officially part of the League. 

Ready to join?

Explore our certification criteria to ensure your work makes the cut. We’ll take care of the rest.

FAQ

How do I get certified? 

Our certification program is designed to let your expertise and hard work speak for itself. We have high standard criteria for each certification that validates your expertise. To become certified make sure you mark through the criteria as you focus on your client work and we'll make sure to certify you once you are eligible. Each month we will announce and celebrate the creators who are eligible for certifications in their field.

Do I need to apply for a certification?

You can no longer apply to the Wix Studio’s Certifications. Certifications are based on internal review, designed to recognize and celebrate the skills you demonstrate on Wix Studio every day.

Are the Wix Studio certifications free?

Yes, certifications are completely free and industry-recognized. With over 258M users, your new certified status can help attract more leads and future clients.

What do I gain by being Wix Studio certified?

By becoming certified by Wix Studio, you’ll be recognized by your peers and potential clients as an expert in your field. With this recognition and leader status, you’ll receive a certificate and badge that you can add to your agency site and social profile. The certification helps validate your credibility in the Wix Marketplace and across the industry.

Is the certification validated?

Yes, each certification comes with an individual ID that is validated on a dedicated Wix Studio page, allowing others to confirm its authenticity.

What are Wix Studio’s Certification Terms and Conditions?

To maintain your Certification, you must continuously meet the applicable Certification criteria, which may be updated periodically on this page, and comply with the Wix Terms of Use.

 

Wix reserves the sole discretion to determine the eligibility criteria, benefits, and selection of Certified users. Wix may revoke the Certification attributed to you, at its sole discretion without notice or liability to you, if it determines, in its sole discretion, that (a) your conduct or actions may harm Wix’s reputation, the integrity of the Certification program, or the Certification granted to you; (b) you are no longer meeting the applicable Certification requirements and criteria; or (c) you breached the Wix Terms of Use.

 

Wix reserves the right to modify, suspend or terminate the Certification program, including any and all benefits provided, at any time, for any reason, with or without prior notice, without incurring any liability to you.
